Tri-Quarter Theorem Animation v1.0
# Authors: Nathan O. Schmidt and Grok
# Created Date: March 7, 2025
# Modified Date: March 7, 2025
# Requirements: Python 3.8+, matplotlib, numpy
# Note: Works good with Python 3.13 on Fedora 41 Linux and Windows 11, should be fine on Python 3.8+ elsewhere.

Assuming that you've already downloaded tri_quarter.py and installed Python 3.8+ on your box...

[Fedora Linux]
 --> Bust out your favorite terminal.
 --> Install: `sudo dnf install python3-pip`
 --> Install: `pip install matplotlib numpy`
 --> Install: `sudo dnf install python3-tkinter`
 --> Execute: `python3 tri_quarter.py`

[Windows]
 --> Download: https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py
 --> Bust out powershell or good ole command prompt.
 --> Install: `python3 get-pip.py`
 --> Install: `pip install matplotlib numpy`
 --> Execute: `python3 tri_quarter.py`

[macOS]
 --> Download: https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py
 --> Bust out your terminal.
 --> Install: `pip install matplotlib numpy`
 --> Execute: `python3 tri_quarter.py`
